## Consulting in the Age of AI

AI is changing the consulting conversation in important ways:

**New stakeholder expectations:**
Stakeholders are increasingly aware of AI capabilities 
and may arrive with unrealistic expectations about 
speed and cost. Help them understand:
- AI accelerates production, not diagnosis
- Faster content generation doesn't eliminate 
  the need for needs analysis
- AI-generated content still requires expert 
  review and instructional judgment

**New questions to ask:**
- *"Is there an AI-powered performance support solution 
  that would serve learners better than a course here?"*
- *"Could this be addressed with an intelligent job aid 
  rather than formal training?"*
- *"What data do we have about actual performance 
  that AI could help us analyze?"*

**New credibility opportunities:**
IDs who understand AI's role in learning — and can 
advise stakeholders on when and how to use it — 
are increasingly valuable strategic partners.

