## Common Stakeholder Management Mistakes

- **Accepting the stated solution without diagnosis** — 
  building what's asked for instead of what's needed
- **Avoiding difficult conversations** — short-term 
  comfort, long-term credibility damage
- **Over-promising on timelines** — sets up failure 
  and erodes trust
- **Disappearing during production** — stakeholders 
  who don't hear from you assume something is wrong
markdown
- **Presenting only one option** — giving stakeholders 
  a choice between two or three approaches increases 
  buy-in and ownership
- **Treating SMEs as obstacles** — they're partners; 
  your job is to channel their expertise, not bypass it
- **Skipping the kickoff conversation** — assumptions 
  made at the start compound into expensive problems later

